cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The task of extreme summarization also involves information retrieval and understanding, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for modeling and optimization could also suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
